                <note rend="inline" type="source">124.83/87: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Minister in Egypt</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Kirk</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1942-06-29T18:00:00-04:00"
                            >June 29, 1942—6 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>634. In response to last paragraph of your 1091, June 27, you are informed that
                    Department’s 602, June 23 was intended to give you in your discretion full
                    authority regarding your movements and those of American diplomatic and consular
                    personnel in Egypt.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
